    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overruns in FAPI P7 message comparison functions\n\n### Summary\nThe FAPI P7 message comparison functions in nr_fapi_p7_utils.c contained multiple buffer overruns when comparing structures with array fields. The bug manifested when message fields indicating array sizes exceeded the fixed-size array bounds defined in the NFAPI specifications.\n\nSpecifically, the functions eq_dl_tti_beamforming(), eq_ul_tti_beamforming(), and several others were accessing arrays beyond their allocated size when the num_* fields contained values larger than the fixed array dimensions.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Added bounds checking in beamforming comparison functions\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Added bounds checking in PUSCH data comparison functions  \n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Added bounds checking in UCI indication comparison functions\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Added bounds checking in PRACH indication comparison functions\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Added bounds checking in TX data request comparison functions\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Added bounds checking in PDCCH PDU comparison functions\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Added bounds checking in DL TTI request comparison functions\n- Similar bounds checks added to copy and dump functions for consistency\n\nThe buffer overruns could be triggered by sending malformed FAPI messages with num_prgs, num_dig_bf_interfaces, num_cb, num_harq, num_preamble, num_TLV, numDlDci, or nPDUs fields set to values exceeding the fixed array sizes (NFAPI_MAX_NUM_PRGS, NFAPI_MAX_NUM_BG_IF, NFAPI_MAX_NUM_CB, etc.). This could lead to memory corruption and unpredictable behavior in the gNB.\n"
}